    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Warp pile weave, typically silk, with a short, soft dense pile produced by a supplementary warp that is raised in loops above the surface of the textile through the introduction of rods during the weaving; the loops may be cut or left uncut.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
